      • getPlantType

        public static EnumPlantType getPlantType(java.lang.String name)
        Getting a custom EnumPlantType, or an existing one if it has the same name as that one. Your plant should implement IPlantable and return this custom type in IPlantable.getPlantType(IBlockAccess, BlockPos).

        If your new plant grows on blocks like any one of them above, never create a new EnumPlantType. This enumeration is only functioning in Block.canSustainPlant(IBlockState, IBlockAccess, BlockPos, EnumFacing, IPlantable), which you are supposed to override this function in your new block and create a new plant type to grow on that block.

        You can create an instance of your plant type in your API and let your/others mods access it. It will be faster than calling this method.

        参数:
        name - the name of the type of plant, you had better follow the style above
        返回:
        the acquired EnumPlantType, a new one if not found.
